I'm going to respect you by giving you real criticism. So understand everything I say isn't an attack.

You start off with cold dialogue between unknown entities, you've clearly thought about these characters but your audience knows nothing. You need to reexamine how you present those characters to your audience. Actually a lot of your dialogue is ambiguous there are many points where people can be easily confused about who is saying what. There's nothing wrong with typing "X said" in between three lines of quotes to clarify who is talking. You'll find more adjectives to replace "said" as you write more.

The dialogues is good. But avoid the random exclamations
>Sploosh!!!!
>Fuck
These are the sort of things you see in movie narration but they only serve to interrupt prose. Its better to describe scenery or the emotion of the characters in focus rather than rely on comic book like declarations.

Personally
>tall girl
>sweet ending
I like. The above criticisms are technical in nature. I like the overall story and how you got there. Very good first writing attempt. I know its hard to look at your work with new eyes, but always remind yourself that the reader is seeing things with total ignorance, you can use that or fall victim to it, so long as you are aware of it.
